  "notes": "Primary source: official RFEG club page (hole-by-hole par, hcp, meters per tee, and Vc/Vs ratings). Internal consistency verified: pars sum 36+35=71; stroke indexes are a permutation of 1-18 (odd SI on front nine, even on back); each tee's 18 distances sum exactly to its published total. Cross-check: The Social Golfer's 'yellow tee' card matches RFEG Amarillas per-hole distances and pars exactly (its 'yards' label is mislabeled meters), but its stroke indexes differ on 6 holes (1,5,13,16,17,18); golfingholiday.com carries an older/different card (yardages, different SI) and was disregarded. RFEG's SI allocation is used as authoritative. Discrepancy: RFEG rates the Rosas recorrido at par 70 (back nine 34) despite the standard card being par 71 — likely one back-nine hole (probably 10, 298 m) plays as par 4 from Rosas; per-hole Rosas pars were not itemized, so the holes array reflects the standard par-71 card. Rosas is a pink tee; 'red' is the closest allowed color. RFEG also lists a separate 18-hole par-3 'Verdes' recorrido (1926 m, par 54, Vc/Vs 54.8/71 men, 52.9/62 women) without per-hole data, omitted here as it is not the main course."
